div.p:
Thus the Guiſian party in France ſtrengthened their ſide by their holy League;

and the perfidious party of the Scots, in imitation of them, (and 'tis probable by the French advice) play'd their Pranks under the ſame Vizard;
You may read their palpable Hypocriſie and Jugling, in the King's large Declaration. by which they intended, eſpecially the Ringleaders of the Faction (whatever they pretended) to ſtrengthen the hands of their Party, and by the ſtricteſt tyes of Religion, to engage incautelous Souls in one of the moſt villanous Rebellions that ever was hatched in Hell, or acted on Earth: And yet all this while (ſee the villany of it!) many of the Contrivers had a ſecret reſerve and reſolution to keep it no further or longer than it ſhould be ſubſervient to their own ambitious and covetous ends. Witneſs their baſe, barbarous, and treacherous delivery up of the King's perſon (whom they were bound by the Law of Nature, Nations, and common Humanity, to have protected) into the hands of his cruel and bloud-thirſty Enemies.
